io.vertx.ext.sql

Class ResultSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.vertx.ext.sql.ResultSet

  • public class ResultSet
extends Object
    Represents the results of a SQL query.

    It contains a list for the column names of the results, and a list of JsonArray - one for each row of the results.

    Author:
    Tim Fox

      • getRows

        public List<JsonObject> getRows()
        Get the rows - each row represented as a JsonObject where the keys are the column names and the values are the column values. Beware that it's legal for a query result in SQL to contain duplicate column names, in which case one will overwrite the other if using this method. If that's the case use getResults() instead. Be aware that column names are defined as returned by the database, this means that even if your SQL statement is for example: 
        SELECT a, b FROM table
        the column names are not required to be: 
        a
        and 
        b
        and could be in fact 
        A
        and 
        B
        . For cases when there is the need for case insentivitity you should see getRows(boolean)
        Returns:
        the rows represented as JSON object instances

      • getRows

        public List<JsonObject> getRows(boolean caseInsensitive)
        Get the rows - each row represented as a JsonObject where the keys are the column names and the values are the column values. Beware that it's legal for a query result in SQL to contain duplicate column names, in which case one will overwrite the other if using this method. If that's the case use getResults() instead. Special note, when encoding the row JSON to a String or Buffer the column names will be as they returned by the database server regardless of the case sensitivity chosen on this method call.
        Parameters:
        caseInsensitive - - treat column names as case insensitive, i.e.: FoO equals foo equals FOO
        Returns:
        the rows represented as JSON object instances
